Intro

An indicator used to show the current position for respective object or element.

Four types of Cursors:

    -> Enumeration
    -> Iterator
    -> ListIterator
    -> Spliterator

1) Enumeration

    Used For: Legacy class' objects
    Legacy: Yes
    Direction Flow: Forward
    Access we can get: Only Read
    Object Creation: By using elements() method of Vector class
    Methods: hasMoreElements(), nextElement()

2) Iterator

    Used For: For any collection object
    Legacy: No
    Direction Flow: Forward
    Access we can get: Read and Remove
    Object Creation: By using iterator() method of Collection interface
    Methods: hasNext(), next(), remove()

3) ListIterator

    Used For: For list class' objects
    Legacy: No
    Direction Flow: Forward and Backward
    Access we can get: Read, Remove, Replace and Add
    Object Creation: By using listiterator() method of List interface
    Methods: hasNext(), next(), nextIndex(), hasPrevious(), previous(),
        previousIndex(), remove(), add(Object o), set(Object o)